about.summary: Accurately separate the TLD from the registered domain andsubdomains of a URL, using the Public Suffix List.

name: tldextract
raw_recipe:
{%set name = "tldextract" %}
{%set version = "2.0.1" %}
{%set compress_type = "tar.gz" %}
{%set hash_type = "sha256" %}
{%set hash_val = "ad4e07999142b9effc29d5a5c762f85cfe04f90f681d3b3729ac09616b4d61d6" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: {{ name }}-{{ version }}.{{ compress_type }}
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.{{ compress_type }}
  {{ hash_type }}: {{ hash_val }}

build:
  preserve_egg_dir: True
  entry_points:
    - tldextract = tldextract.cli:main
  number: 0
  script: python setup.py install --single-version-externally-managed --record=record.txt

requirements:
  build:
    - python
    - setuptools

  run:
    - python
    - setuptools
    - idna
    - requests >=2.1.0
    - requests-file >=1.4

test:
  imports:
    - tldextract

  commands:
    - tldextract --help

about:
  home: https://github.com/john-kurkowski/tldextract
  license: BSD 3-Clause
  # license_file: LICENSE not in MANIFEST - see https://github.com/john-kurkowski/tldextract/pull/108
  license_family: BSD
  summary: 'Accurately separate the TLD from the registered domain andsubdomains of a URL, using the Public Suffix List.'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - pmlandwehr
